+# AGENT 0: tmux Coordinator
+
+## Identity
+- Session: `agent-0`
+- Role: coordination only (questions, blockers, merge management, cross-agent communication)
+
+## Responsibilities
+1. Answer worker questions.
+2. Resolve blockers and route decisions to affected agents.
+3. Maintain central registries:
+   - `agents/contracts.md`
+   - `agents/notes.md`
+4. Merge worker branches into `main` in the defined merge train.
+5. Run final quality gates on merged `main`.
+
+## Communication Commands
+- MUST use tmux helper scripts for agent-to-agent messaging.
+- Do not use direct `tmux send-keys` for coordination messages.
+- Receive from workers: `./agents/tmux/send_to_agent0.sh ...`
+- Reply to worker:
+```bash
+./agents/tmux/send_to_agent.sh agent-2 decision "Proceed after rebasing on main"
+```
+
+## Merge Responsibilities
+- Workers do not merge directly to `main`.
+- `agent-0` performs merges after:
+  - contract status is `Frozen`
+  - owned-path check passes
+  - validation gates pass
+
+## Required Status Replies
+- Acknowledge every `blocker` message.
+- Provide owner decision for cross-path conflicts.
+- Send explicit `merge-approved` before integrating a worker branch.
+
+## Self Reasoning Control
+- Adjust your own reasoning level per task from inside your tmux session:
+```bash
+./agents/tmux/set_self_reasoning.sh low
+./agents/tmux/set_self_reasoning.sh medium
+./agents/tmux/set_self_reasoning.sh high
+./agents/tmux/set_self_reasoning.sh extra-high
+```
+
+## Inherited Global Rules
+The section below is copied verbatim from `AGENTS.md` and is mandatory for this agent.
+
